Job detailsHere’s how the job details align with your profile.Job typeFull-time&nbsp;LocationMumbai, Maharashtra&nbsp;Full job descriptionAbout the Role
We are seeking a dedicated Data Analyst who is enthusiastic about shaping and maintaining a robust and scalable data platform. In this pivotal role, you will collaborate with various teams across the organization to bolster business strategies and enhance decision-making processes. Your expertise will be instrumental in solving numerous business challenges through the creation of meticulously designed dashboards and reports.
Responsibilities
Data Modeling:&nbsp;Develop and take ownership of data models that underpin our business intelligence solutions.&nbsp;
SQL Proficiency: Write, understand, and troubleshoot intricate SQL statements, leveraging your deep knowledge to analyze data, uncover anomalies, and address performance bottlenecks.&nbsp;
Reporting Solutions: Design and implement pragmatic solutions for complex reporting needs, applying data modeling techniques and industry best practices to enable self-service and automated reporting.&nbsp;
Requirements Analysis: Conduct thorough requirements gathering and analysis to ensure the delivery of tailored and effective business intelligence solutions.&nbsp;
Reporting and Visualization: Develop and maintain a diverse range of reports, dashboards, and visualizations using tools like PowerBI and other reporting platforms.&nbsp;
Information Automation: Create personalized reports and alerts, streamlining information delivery to both management and technical teams.&nbsp;
Business Insight Gathering: Understand and gather business needs for data insights that empower informed decision-making.&nbsp;
BI Tool Development:&nbsp;Craft engaging dashboards and reports within various BI tools.&nbsp;
ETL Development: Implement Extract, Transform, Load (ETL) processes in various cloud solutions to ensure data integrity and accessibility.&nbsp;
Performance Optimization: Optimize Power BI data sources for enhanced performance, usability, and interpretability.
Competencies
Database Expertise: Possess a strong knowledge of SQL, DAX, and M language to effectively work with data.&nbsp;
Data Storytelling: Grasp the concepts of data storytelling to convey insights clearly and effectively.&nbsp;
Communication Skills: Exhibit excellent communication skills in English (B2+ level) to interact and collaborate effectively with stakeholders.&nbsp;
Excel Mastery:&nbsp;Showcase an expert understanding of Microsoft Excel.&nbsp;
PowerBI Prowess: Demonstrate advanced proficiency in PowerBI for report creation and visualization, including mastery of data integration and transformation using Power Query.&nbsp;
DAX Wizardry:&nbsp;Prove your ability to write complex DAX metrics for robust data analysis.&nbsp;
Data Integration: Be well-versed in methods and best practices for combining data from various sources, importing, and transforming data using Power Query.&nbsp;
Cloud Data Warehouses: Familiarity with Azure Synapse, Google BigQuery, and Amazon RedShift is a plus.&nbsp;
Bonus Skills: Previous experience with Elasticsearch/Kibana is an added advantage.&nbsp;
Qualifications:&nbsp;

